The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has approved the conduct of the Party’s North West Zonal Congress to elect Zonal Executive Officers and National Ex-Officio in the North West Zone. PDP in a statement by its National Publicity Secretary, Debo Ologunagba, Saturday explained that the exercise is scheduled to hold on Monday, May 9, 2022, at the Zonal Headquarters, Kaduna, Kaduna State. The opposition party’s NWC requests all leaders, critical stakeholders and its teeming members in the North-West to be guided accordingly for a smooth and hitch-free exercise. PDP assured that the North West Zonal Congress will be conducted in line with the Constitution and Guidelines of the Party, and in adherence to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) Protocol on COVID-19.